.SH Version 19.10.0 (2014\-08\-06)
.PP
This release improves responsiveness and adds a command to list failed files.
.SS Minor:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.BR tork-engine (1): 
list most recently ran test files in \fB\fC:idle\fR event.  This
allows 
.BR tork (1) 
to summarize a run after tests finish running, as follows:
.PP
.RS
.nf
tork: 10 tested, 10 passed, 0 failed
.fi
.RE
.IP \(bu 2
.BR tork-engine (1): 
add \fB\fClist_failed_test_files\fR command that lists all test
files that have failed during their most recent run.
.PP
.BR tork (1): 
add \fB\fCl\fR key (bound to the \fB\fClist_failed_test_files\fR command).
.PP
Thanks to Chris Scharf for contributing this feature in issue\-60:
\[la]https://github.com/sunaku/tork/pull/60\[ra]
.RE
.SS Patch:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
tork/config: auto\-detect \fB\fC$TORK_CONFIGS\fR values only once per session.
This makes Tork load configuration helpers faster on slow file\-systems.
.IP \(bu 2
Use block\-form of Dir.glob() to react more quickly on slow file\-systems.
This makes 
.BR tork-driver (1)'s 
\fB\fCrun_all_test_files\fR command more responsive.
.RE
.SS Other:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Align error/help message wording with manual pages.
.RE
.SH Version 19.9.0 (2014\-07\-17)
.SS Minor:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Add support for testing outside \fB\fCtest/\fR and \fB\fCspec/\fR directories.  This
change lets you run test files directly from the current working directory
without having to put them inside special \fB\fCtest/\fR and \fB\fCspec/\fR directories.
.PP
This can be useful if you are learning Ruby or writing tests for simple
scripts because you need not create a directory structure that is fit for
a larger application just for the sole purpose of running your tests!
.IP \(bu 2
Drop the \fB\fCdefault\fR configuration helper and load the \fB\fCconfig.rb\fR files of
all configuration helpers on startup instead.  This way, each helper can
itself detect whether it is needed from inside its own \fB\fCconfig.rb\fR file.
.IP \(bu 2
Censor Tork internals from test failure backtraces so that users can
inspect them quickly to find where errors are arising in their code.
.RE
.SS Patch:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Only 1 worker was being used on a dual\-core system.
.RE
.SS Other:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.BR tork (1): 
use complete sentences in the help message.
.RE
