.SH Version 19.8.1 (2014\-06\-28)
.SS Patch:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.BR tork-driver (1): 
sanitize the file paths reported by 
.BR tork-herald (1).
.PP
This allows a user to override 
.BR tork-herald (1) 
with their own program
that reports changed file paths in a less than ideal, but valid, way.
For example, with relative directory traversals and redundant slashes.
.IP \(bu 2
.BR tork-remote (1): 
deal with stale server socket files; don't just exit.
.PP
A stale socket file is left behind by a server that was prematurely
killed so it should be safe to delete it and start up a new server.
.IP \(bu 2
tork/server: ensure that 
.BR tork-remote (1) 
gets the same ARGV we did.
.RE
.SS Other:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Rename \fB\fC*.md\fR file extension to the full \fB\fC*.markdown\fR\&.
.IP \(bu 2
README: link to manuals index; demote package link.
.RE
.SH Version 19.8.0 (2014\-06\-23)
.SS Minor:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Add \fB\fCbundler\fR configuration helper to load a bundle into 
.BR tork-master (1).
.PP
This lets you run Tork inside any application that uses Bundler without
having to first add Tork to its \fB\fCGemfile\fR and then \fB\fCbundle install\fR it.
In fact, installing the Tork gem \fIoutside\fP of the bundle is sufficient.
.PP
Try it: go into a bundled application and call \fB\fCtork\fR to run its tests!
.RE
.SS Patch:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Server: fix crash when Fixnum is sent as a message.
.PP
.RS
.nf
lib/tork/server.rb:45:in `block (2 levels) in loop':
undefined method `empty?' for 6:Fixnum (NoMethodError)
lib/tork/cliapp.rb:59:in `recv':
undefined method `lstrip' for 6:Fixnum (NoMethodError)
.fi
.RE
.PP
Because JSON.load() and JSON.parse() are different:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ irb \-r json
>> JSON.load '6'
6
>> JSON.parse '6'
JSON::ParserError: A JSON text must at least contain two octets!
        from /usr/lib/ruby/2.1.0/json/common.rb:155:in `initialize'
        from /usr/lib/ruby/2.1.0/json/common.rb:155:in `new'
        from /usr/lib/ruby/2.1.0/json/common.rb:155:in `parse'
        from (irb):2
        from /usr/bin/irb:11:in `<main>'
.fi
.RE
.RE
.SS Other:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Upgrade to md2man 3.0 for improved HTML manuals.
.RE
