.SH Version 19.0.0 (2012\-10\-17)
.SS Major:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
The \fB\fC\&.tork.rb\fR configuration file has been replaced by the \fB\fC\&.tork/\fR
directory, which contains specially\-named Ruby scripts.  Refer to the
\fB\fCTORK_CONFIGS\fR environment variable in 
.BR tork (1) 
for more information.
.IP \(bu 2
The \fB\fCTork::Config\fR object has been replaced by various data structures in
the \fB\fCTork::\fR namespace.  See the "FILES" sections in the manual pages of
tork programs for information on the data structures that replaced it.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\fCTork::Config.test_event_hooks\fR has been removed.  Instead, you must now
monitor the STDOUT of 
.BR tork-master (1) 
or 
.BR tork-engine (1) 
either directly
or indirectly, via 
.BR tork-remote (1), 
and react to their status messages.
See the 
.BR tork-notify (1) 
program for an example of how to implement this.
.IP \(bu 2
.BR tork (1): 
't' now runs a specified test, whereas 'a' runs all tests.
.IP \(bu 2
.BR tork-engine (1): 
the \fB\fCrun_test_file\fR command now takes line numbers as a
variable\-length list of arguments (varargs) rather than as an array.
.IP \(bu 2
.BR tork-engine (1): 
the \fB\fCrun_test_file\fR command now runs an entire test file
when zero is given as one of the line numbers to be run.
.IP \(bu 2
.BR tork-master (1): 
the \fB\fCload\fR command is no longer accepted.  Instead, you
must specify load paths and overhead files in the \fB\fC\&.tork/master.rb\fR file.
.IP \(bu 2
The \fB\fCTORK_CONFIGS\fR env\-var is now a colon delimited list of directories.
.IP \(bu 2
The \fB\fCtork/client\fR library has been removed.  The threaded IO and popen()
wrappers that it provided have been replaced by the powerful IO.select().
.RE
.SS Minor:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.BR tork (1): 
allow user to specify arguments after command key
.IP \(bu 2
.BR tork (1): 
add 'k' to stop all currently running tests with SIGKILL
.IP \(bu 2
add 
.BR tork-remote (1) 
to remotely control any tork program.  This feature is
made possible by the awesome power of IO.select() and UNIX domain sockets.
.IP \(bu 2
add 
.BR tork-notify (1) 
as example of using 
.BR tork-remote (1) 
and 
.BR tork-engine (1)
.IP \(bu 2
.BR tork-engine (1): 
add \fB\fC["run_test_files"]\fR command to run multiple files
.IP \(bu 2
.BR tork-engine (1): 
emit edge\-triggered \fB\fCpass_now_fail\fR and \fB\fCfail_now_pass\fR
events to notify you about changes in a test file's pass/fail status.
.IP \(bu 2
typing Control\-D now breaks tork programs out of \fB\fCTork::Server#loop()\fR
.RE
.SS Patch:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.BR tork-master (1): 
stop workers with SIGKILL when quitting
.RE
.SS Other:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.BR tork (1): 
document parameters for \fB\fCt\fR and \fB\fCs\fR commands
.IP \(bu 2
README: add tip about rlwrap for better interactive
.IP \(bu 2
README: simplify watch command using pgrep & xargs
.IP \(bu 2
README: use standard bundle exec; no \fB\fC\-\-binstubs\fR
.RE
